<!-- INTRO -->
<section class="about-intro">
    <p>
        Every Filipino deserves roads that don’t flood, schools that don’t leak, water 
        systems that don’t break, and public projects that are finished, not forgotten.
        Infrastructure Watch PH was founded to make sure these basic needs are no longer ignored.
    </p>
    <p>
        After all, the Philippines’ infrastructure is the backbone of daily life. 
        Yet as cities expand, many provinces and barangays continue to struggle with:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Unpaved, impassable roads during rainy season</li>
        <li>Broken or non-existent water systems</li>
        <li>Half-built school buildings and health centers</li>
        <li>Drainage systems that overflow with the first rain</li>
    </ul>
    <p>  
        These aren’t just “inconveniences”, they affect farmers’ livelihoods, 
        students’ education, and families’ health. <b>We</b> will shine a 
        light on these issues so citizens can demand better.
    </p>
</section>

